      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LIFE'S A JOURNEY (8) drawn the outside box and could get a clear run. Was below best last time when 8th and beaten 15 lengths at Angle Park (31.41). Goes very well at course and distance boasting one wins. Has performed well from this box with a win and four minor placings to his name from eight starts. Better than last start and worth following up. MAKE SOME NOISE (1) placed two runs ago then again in the money last time when third (22.63) at this track in a Grade 3/4/5. Has good speed and is aided by the cherry draw. Rates a winning chance on best. TOORA TERRY (6) is better than last start when fifth (19.81) from Box 6 at Angle Park over 342m. The form from his last run stacks up well. Shapes as one to consider. DIRTY DASH (2) has claims again if he runs up to the latest effort.",
